RSS Feed of notes in a bbox

Source: R/map_notes.R
osm_feed_notes.Rd

RSS Feed of notes in a bbox

Usage

osm_feed_notes(bbox)

Arguments

bbox

Coordinates for the area to retrieve the notes from (left,bottom,right,top). Floating point numbers in degrees, expressing a valid bounding box.

See also

Other notes' functions: osm_read_bbox_notes(), osm_read_note(), osm_search_notes()

Other GET calls: osm_api_versions(), osm_bbox_objects(), osm_capabilities(), osm_details_logged_user(), osm_details_users(), osm_details_user(), osm_download_changeset(), osm_fetch_objects(), osm_full_object(), osm_get_data_gpx(), osm_get_metadata_gpx(), osm_get_points_gps(), osm_history_object(), osm_list_gpxs(), osm_permissions(), osm_query_changesets(), osm_read_bbox_notes(), osm_read_changeset(), osm_read_note(), osm_read_object(), osm_relations_object(), osm_search_notes(), osm_version_object(), osm_ways_node()

Examples

feed_notes <- osm_feed_notes(bbox = c(0.8205414, 40.6686604, 0.8857727, 40.7493377))
## bbox as a character value also works. Equivalent call:
# feed_notes <- osm_feed_notes(bbox = "0.8205414,40.6686604,0.8857727,40.7493377")
